body.job_description:
Initial Inspection and Safety Assessment:
Our technicians begin with an inspection of your windows to assess their condition and identify any specific cleaning needs or challenges.  Additionally, as safety is our top priority, we inspect the work environment and carefully evaluate the site to ensure all safety standards are met, or can readily be addressed.

We strive to maintain a low profile and minimize disruptions to your day, whether at home or business. To access the window glass effectively, we will remove window screens and any other obstructions that may hinder our cleaning process. Common obstructions include shutters, awnings, window decorations, and furniture positioned near windows. We will likely need to go inside your home to access and remove window screens and any other obstructions safely and efficiently. Additionally, we avoid setting up equipment over doorways, walkways, and in high-traffic areas to prevent creating tripping hazards and other dangerous situations. Our preparations ensure a seamless and unobtrusive cleaning process.

Window Cleaning:
We start by applying a biodegradable cleaning solution that effectively breaks down dirt and stubborn deposits, ensuring an eco-friendly cleaning process that is safe for the environment, pets, and people. Using a soft-bristle brush, we gently scrub the window surfaces to lift off stubborn dirt and debris without scratching the glass. We expertly use a squeegee to remove the cleaning solution, leaving the windows streak-free and crystal clear. Edges and corners are wiped down with microfiber cloths to ensure no water spots or streaks are left behind. Frames and sills are also cleaned for a complete finish, enhancing the overall appearance of your windows.

Gleams Exterior Window Washing Service is committed to providing exceptional results with minimal disruption to your daily activities. Our professional and meticulous approach ensures your windows are left spotless and shining, contributing to the overall beauty and clarity of your property.
